caption: They really nail everything here. The sandwiches are really bold and flavorful, and their fries are anything but boring. The truffle BLT and seasame fries are my go-to order.

I got the truffle BLT and spicy sesame fries at the recommendation of Sarah. WOW. The flavor of the BLT is next level, and the smell is intoxicating. The portions were huge, and as someone with an appetite I could only finish half. The fries sauce taste like the spicy mayo one puts on sushi. I’ll 100% be back. Totally worth 10 for the Sandwich, especially if you love blts!
Price is slightly on the higher end, but everything was so yummy! Portion is huge too.
Loved their truffle blt! I don’t even usually like sandwich.
Great food
Although they serve greasy foods/fries, food quality is good and prices are reasonable.
First time here.  Tasty turkey sandwich and great spicy sesame fries for lunch on a surprisingly warm November afternoon.
Thoughtful, simple, easy and delicious.
Buffalo chicken and the giant cookie are to die for

I've always loved Fat Shallot's food truck, but then we stopped by their store and had a frozen gin and tonic and they made my son a grilled cheese with bacon. The universe was in complete order for 18 minutes
I got the avocado turkey sandwich. It was very good with their house fries....fries were to salty.  Service was very good but they did not take cash.
Delicious every time.

This place is SO GOOD. My favorite shelter-in-place treat lunch (or dinner) is the buffalo chicken sandwich with the spicy sesame fries. Delicious!! It's a small menu with basics done so right, and I'd highly recommend giving them a try for delivery or carryout.

Where to begin?!!? Amazing sandwiches - just hard to choose between the Reuben, the BLT, and the gourmet grilled cheese! These are a big step up from regular sandwiches with top-notch ingredients and taste. Also, that gin and tonic slushie should not be missed!!! Yum!  I'm writing this during covid-19 so also worth noting that their window pickup works very well with no contact required. Love this place!!!
Amazing food and great staff at Lincoln park. Visit at least once a week
The food is sooo good here! They've even rolled out a vegan Reuben sandwich. Perfect place in Chicago for amazing sandwiches!
Good food. Good atmosphere. Cool people :)

It deserves that 4.8 rating. Granted, I was the only customer in there at the time due to weather, but the counter guy couldn't have been more personable and the grilled cheese (a bit of an understatement, as it has sauteed spinach and carmelized onions along for the ride) and rosemary fries were great as was the store-made lemonade. A bit pricy - no boutique sandwich shop isn't - but completely worth the money for quality American comfort food. They also have adult beverages ranging from beer to shots as well.
The best!!
Friendly and delicious!
Good food and amazing service. Got the Ruben, truffle fries, and a salad.
Excellent sandwiches. Out of the ordinary flavor, quality, value
It was alright. Good basic grilled cheese but not special
Fantastic service. EXCELLENT food! Great value!
Amazing sandwiches, fries and bacon potato salad.  The gin and tonic slushee alone is worth visiting this perfect sandwich shop.  Can’t wait to come back.
I would say the food is okay it is overpriced and not a lot of options
The food is fresh and delicious! I can't wait to go back! Great service too!
Excellent sandwich

Awesome experience. We can highly recommend the buffalo chicken sandwich and the chilaquile nachos. They were both amazing! Big portions, and also great beer selection. The giant chocolate chip cookie is an awesome dessert.
Delicious sandwiches

Hit the spot the BLT was really good and the price of the food was a great deal. The costumer service was great the two people working there were extremely nice and helpful and overall it was a 5 star meal so I would highly recommend this place for lunch any day.
Unique twist on old favorites, fun atmosphere, patio seating, friendly service
Amazing fries and the sandwich was great too!! Get the truffle fries!!!

The sandwiches are quite good and aren't unnecessarily huge. The buffalo chicken is great, not very spicy but enough of a kick. The BLT is also tasty, but a little heavy on the aioli. Rosemary fries are also delicious and you get a big basket for $3. Staff are friendly and helpful and it's quick to get your order.
Best sandwich in Lincoln Park!
Good prices, good food, chill atmosphere. Got the grilled cheese on a pretzel bun... the best pretzel bun I've ever had. The bread as a whole is fantastic.
Excellent sandwiches, and a really nice ginger lemonade. Cute spot to grab a bite on the way to the zoo.
Pretty solid sandwich place. I would recommend it if you're in the area. I haven't found a better sandwich shop between Fullerton and Diversey (on Clark).
The food is grate and service incredible very helpful when you stop by with kids !!! Thank you.

Not only was the food great, but the service was phenomenal! We will be back for the great sandwiches and also those chocolate chip cookies (so good).  Edit: Came back again. Different people working and still the same level of amazing service. I am so glad I live near this place. I wish I could give more than 5 stars!
So glad that they have a Lincoln park location.The food is great as always.. especially the truffle BLT. The staff is friendly and it's a great place to hang out!

Tasty little sandwich spot in Lincoln Park!  I tried the Rueben and my husband had the Buffalo chicken sandwich. The Rueben is copious! Thick slices of yummy corned beef covered with spicy sauce made for a decadent treat. The chicken sandwich was made of 5 breaded chicken tenders tossed in buffalo sauce, with blue cheese and a celery slaw salad. Both sandwiches were huge and filling, maybe even a little unwieldy because of their size.  We also had fries with truffle sauce to top it off. The fries are well fried and tasty. The truffle sauce is sinful and too easy eat!  They also serve alcohol, but we didn't try any. The place is clean and well designed. The music was great, while we ate at some point the song, There is a Light that Never Goes Out by the Smiths. That was nice.

Great brick and mortar outpost of the hit food truck. All your favorites are here, including the truffle BLT and that oh so good turkey sandwich.  They also have beer and liquor, including a G&T slushie machine!
People were awesome as they always are in Chicago. Food not terrible, just a little busy. Great food ideas taken just a bit too far.
Food is a bit pricier than I was expecting but I kid you not the buffalo chicken sandwich was one of the best sandwiches I've ever had. Can't wait to try the rest of the menu!
The BLTs are great! Well worth the trip
The gin and tonic slushies are a dream so is the tasty food. I had the yummy grilled cheese and fries, I could swim in their garlic aioli.
Love it!
The best sandwich place in Lincoln Park. The BLT is to die for. They recently had a pot roast sandwich that I wish was on the regular menu during the fall/winter months.

The quality of this food surpasses some of the best restaurants in the city.  Every sandwich on this menu is the best sandwich I've ever had. Ever. I am updating this now that I've had everything on the menu.  And not just the sandwiches - the carrot curry soup blew me away with how complex the flavors were. The quality is incredible but especially for the price. The nicest staff too.
Great sandwiches

I love this restaurant. The food serving is pretty generous. The taste is amazing, especially the truffle BLT. The staff is also friendly. One time, we were curious on one of the appetisers and the staff gave us a sample for us to taste.
Great little place. Comfy Dinner feel that goes well with the food truck comfort style food. A welcome addition to the neighborhood!

Love all their food! Especially the grilled cheese! Customer service is great as well. I made the bonehead move and didn't request my grilled cheese without onions and greens. However they were super chill about it and replaced with no worries. Some may say this place is pricy but you definitely get what you pay for.

If you dont get all kinds of fries, you are doing it wrong! Having been a huge fan for years, I am stoked for the brick and mortar location! the food and drinks cannot be beat! promise we'll be back soon :)

Brick and mortar for a food truck of the same name. It’s got a lot going for it, including location and a relaxed, easy vibe. Portions for the sandwiches are massive, and while they’re expensive they’re quite affordable if you go with the intention to split one. I had the pulled pork, which was OK. The meat was good, but the coleslaw was super peppery and there simply wasn’t enough of it. But I’ve heard the Ruben and the fries are quite good.
Loved the food. Truffle fries were amazing!
Best BLT I have ever had in my life. Whoever decided to put truffle oil in a blt is not being paid enough.
This place is the ideal neighborhood sandwich joint. Fast, easy, and mouthwatering. They have a perfect sized menu and even booze and soft serve!

I can’t wait to go back.  I ordered the Turkey, sans bacon, to go.   The lady I ordered from was really friendly and brought my sandwich out pretty quickly.   Obviously they make everything to order.  The turkey was served warm while the salad was chilled.   Seriously so good.   The ingredients are really nice quality.  I wanted to gorge myself and eat the entire thing.  But I decided to save half so I could convince my boyfriend how great The Fat Shallot is.  Stop in and try it.

I just had the reuben sandwich, and it was soooo good I wanted to cry! And after it was gone, I wanted cry again lol! This reuben has now taken the top spot on my list of local guilty pleasures. It's going to be tough to try another sandwich there, but I do have to try the BLT.
This is a great space with friendly staff and  a good selection of drinks and food. Service is speedy making it a great place to have a quick bite for a reasonable price.
Have had their Buffalo Chicken sandwich twice, and i think that might be my favorite. Staff is friendly and service is pretty fast.

I had the buffalo chicken sandwich and the slaw. Both were great, especially the buffalo chicken sandwich. The other items on the menu looks great too. There was a lot of place to sit inside and outside, this location is also very convenient if you are reaching here by bus.

Best casual food in the neighborhood! Reasonably priced, especially for the portion size. The buffalo chicken sandwich was delicious, just the right amount of heat. Staff was friendly and very helpful. Ambiance is just what you're looking for with the style of food. Open and airy with the perfect amount of character and details. It was a pleasure to sit and take in the room. Will definitely return.

Sandwiches tasted: grilled cheese - good, pulled pork - very good, reuben - even better. Fries were ok but its truffle seasoning really good: a must. Bourbon iced tea with good punch, ginger lemonade also a must. Reasonable price but what is the best of this place is the warm service!
Great food at a reasonable price. Seriously the pulled pork sandwich is fantastic. This is a welcomed addition to the neighborhood!
